Package objects

Class Ship

java.lang.Object
objects.Ship
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class Ship
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
This object represents a Ship, which stores state such as its length, its name, whether or not it is sunk, its representation, and most importantly how many hits it has taken. In addition, a point is mapped to a ship, so when a hit is made, it is easy to find out exactly which Ship took the hit.
Version:
JDK 14.0.1
Author:
Matthew Ricci
